    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Heavy solid boards of wood used in Buddhist monasteries, struck with a mallet or heavy knotted rope to produce sound. Often inscribed; may be hung or suspended near a door or hall.</Note_Text>
